Dear All,=0A=
=0A=
The difference between a Grothendieck topos and an elementary topos=0A=
is like the difference between a "frame"(=3D a locale) and a Heyting algebr=
a.=0A=
=0A=
A Grothendieck topos should be called a "topos",=0A=
whereas an elementary topos could be called a "logical topos".=0A=
=0A=
Best regards,=0A=
Andr=E9=0A=
=0A=
